#### Intra-Bengal trade

Trade between Bangladesh and India represents the largest bilateral trade relationship in South Asia, with a combined value estimated at US$16 billion. [151] A significant portion of this trade occurs through the highly active [land ports](/Land_port) situated along the [Bangladesh-India border](/Bangladesh-India_border). The [Bangladesh Bhutan India Nepal](/Bangladesh_Bhutan_India_Nepal) Initiative aims to enhance regional trade through a Motor Vehicles Agreement. [152]

### Demographics

